What is the process to invert the color of an entire image?

Inverting the color of an entire image involves converting each pixel to its complementary color. For example, for a pixel with color RGB values (R, G, B), the inverted color would be (255-R, 255-G, 255-B).

What are the general characteristics or visual elements to check for in an inverted image?

When an image is inverted, each color is replaced by its complementary color. This means dark colors will become light colors and vice versa. Additionally, specific hues will change according to their positions on the color wheel. Light colors like light gray will turn into dark colors like dark gray, and distinct colors like orange will turn into blue.
